cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the use of Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) and social network analysis (SNA) in analyzing textual data and social networks, which are commonly studied in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), social informatics (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybernetics (cs.CY). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
